ohha.domain

Class Trial

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohha.domain.Trial

  • public class Trial
extends Object
    This class holds the information of a single trial.
    Author:
    Mikko Tiainen The information kept in the class include the subject who is responding, number of the trial, condition, responses and the response/reaction times. This is basically a storage class, with no logic of its own.

      • Trial

        public Trial(String subject,
             int trialNum,
             String condition,
             List<String> responseNames,
             List<String> responseCodes,
             List<Integer> reactionTimes)
        Create a new Trial with the specified parameters.
        Parameters:
        subject - The subject performing the trial.
        trialNum - Number of the trial in the experiment.
        condition - Condition for the current trial.
        responseNames - Spelled out names of the responses given.
        responseCodes - Response codes for the responses in the trial.
        reactionTimes - Reaction times for the responses.
